                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     EF 142 - Introduction to Physics and Modeling for Engineers II
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     4
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    An introduction to physics concepts for engineering, ways to model these concepts using numerical methods, and skills and practices necessary for a successful engineering career. Topics include work-energy principle, conservation of energy and momentum, application of physics in circular motion, numerical methods applications for modeling highlighted physics concepts, exploration of engineering disciplines, teamwork, project management, and communication skills. Skills learned will include the ability to apply physics concepts to real-world problems, ability to use programming software to model physics concepts, and the ability to recognize and practice concepts related to successful engineering practice such as working in teams, project management, and effective communication.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies Volunteer Core Requirement:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (EI)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     Grading Restriction:
                    </em>
                    Letter grade only.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="EF 141 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184335" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184335'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     EF 141
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    * and
                    <a aria-label="MATH 131 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184018" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184018'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 131
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    .
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Corequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="MATH 132 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184019" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184019'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 132
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Registration Restriction(s):
                    </em>

                    <h3>
                     EF 151 - Physics for Engineers I
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     4
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Calculus-based study of basic physics concepts, including vectors, kinematics, Newton’s laws, forces, work-energy, and impulse-momentum. Introduction to team work. Introduction to the engineering disciplines. Examination of engineering principles and design issues. Oral and written presentation skills.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies Volunteer Core Requirement:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (EI) (NS)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies General Education Requirement through the 2021-2022 academic catalog:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (NS)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Corequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="EF 105 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180899" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180899'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     EF 105
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 101 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184123" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184123'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 101
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 102 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180785" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180785'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ?                      COSC 102
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    ; and
                    <a aria-label="MATH 132 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184019" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184019'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ?                    <div>
                    <h3>
                     PHYS 135 - Introduction to Physics for Physical Science and Mathematics Majors I
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     4
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Calculus-based physics of mechanics, sound, waves, and thermodynamics. May be taught as lecture with lab, integrated lecture and lab, or online with on-campus lab. Check with instructor.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies Volunteer Core Requirement:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (NS)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies General Education Requirement through the 2021-2022 academic catalog:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (NS)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Contact Hour Distribution:
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     3 hours lecture and 2 hours lab.
                    </em>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Corequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="MATH 132 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184019" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184019'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 132
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    * or
                    <a aria-label="MATH 141 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181625" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181625'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 141
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Comment(s):
                    </em>
                    Alternative to
                    <a aria-label="PHYS 137 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182217" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182217'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     PHYS 137
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    * for physics majors.
                    <br/>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 202 - Data Structures and Algorithms I
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     4
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Design, analysis, and implementation of fundamental data structures and algorithms including lists, stacks, queues, hash tables, binary search trees and heaps.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Contact Hour Distribution:
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     3 hours lecture and 1 lab.
                    </em>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 102 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180785" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180785'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 102
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>

                    <h3>
                     COSC 230 - Computer Organization
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Gate level logic, binary number representation and arithmetic, data path and memory hierarchy with focus on code impact, parallel computing, instruction set architecture.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 102 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180785" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180785'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ?                      COSC 102
                    </a>

                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.

                    <h3>
                     MATH 251 - Matrix Algebra I
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    First course in the algebra of simultaneous linear equations and matrices. Includes Gaussian elimination, determinants, vector spaces, linear transformations, eigenvalues, and eigenvectors.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="MATH 142 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181626" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181626'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 142
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>

                    <a aria-label="MATH 148 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181628" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181628'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ?                    <div>
                    <h3>
                     EF 152 - Physics for Engineers II
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     4
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Calculus-based study of basic physics concepts, including rotational dynamics, statics, oscillations, waves, fluids, heat and temperature, and first and second law of thermodynamics. Introduction to team work. Introduction to the engineering disciplines, examination of engineering principles and design issues. Oral and written presentation skills.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies Volunteer Core Requirement:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (EI) (NS)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies General Education Requirement through the 2021-2022 academic catalog:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (NS)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="EF 151 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180901" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180901'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     EF 151
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    * with a grade of C or better, or
                    <a aria-label="EF 142 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184336" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184336'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     EF 142
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    * with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Corequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="MATH 142 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181626" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181626'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 142
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Registration Restriction(s):
                    </em>
                    Tickle College of Engineering or biosystems engineering majors.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     PHYS 136 - Introduction to Physics for Physical Science and Mathematics Majors II
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     4
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Calculus-based physics of electricity, magnetism, and optics. May be taught as lecture with lab, integrated lecture and lab, or online with on-campus lab. Check with instructor.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies Volunteer Core Requirement:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (NS)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies General Education Requirement through the 2021-2022 academic catalog:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (NS)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Contact Hour Distribution:
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     3 hours lecture and 2 hours lab.
                    </em>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="PHYS 135 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182215" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182215'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     PHYS 135
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    * or
                    <a aria-label="PHYS 137 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182217" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182217'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     PHYS 137
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Corequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="MATH 142 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181626" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181626'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 142
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Comment(s):
                    </em>
                    Alternative to
                    <a aria-label="PHYS 138 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182218" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182218'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     PHYS 138
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    * for physics majors.
                    <br/>
                   </div>

                    <h3>
                     COSC 302 - Data Structures and Algorithms II
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     4
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Design, analysis, and implementation of fundamental data structures and algorithms including list and tree-based sorting, graph algorithms and dynamic programming.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Contact Hour Distribution:
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     3 hours lecture and 1 lab.
                    </em>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 202 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184326" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184326'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 202
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>

                    <h3>
                     ECE 313 - Probability and Random Variables
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Probability axioms, Bayes’ theorem. Discrete and continuous random variables. Probability mass functions, density functions, and joint distributions. Central limit theorem. Expectation, variance, covariance, and correlation.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="MATH 142 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181626" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181626'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 142
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    * or
                    <a aria-label="MATH 148 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181628" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181628'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 148
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    * with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 311 - Discrete Structures
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Sets, functions, relations, equivalence relations, partial orderings and proof techniques, especially mathematical induction. Application of proof techniques to prove correctness of algorithms. Introduction to basic counting and combinatorics.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 202 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184326" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184326'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 202
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better, and either

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 360 - Systems Programming
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     4
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    In-depth introduction to C and its use in system programming. Introduction to memory and process layout, system calls, buffering, file I/O, file systems, directories, metadata, assembly code, stack frames, memory management, process management, and interprocess communication.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Contact Hour Distribution:
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     3 hours lecture and 1 lab.
                    </em>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 302 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180789" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180789'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 302
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 307 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182985" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182985'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 307
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better, and either
                    <a aria-label="COSC 230 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184327" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184327'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 230
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="ECE 256 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183938" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183938'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ECE 256
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 101 - Introduction to Programming
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    An introduction to computational thinking and structured programming. Topics include problem solving and algorithm development with emphasis on conditional if/else statements, loop based iteration, and function calls. Students will also be given an overview of commonly used data structures such as arrays. Skills learned include designing a program to solving a problem, developing the algorithms needed, writing code to implement them, testing the code and correcting errors, as well as documenting how the code works.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>
              </div>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 102 - Introduction to Computer Science
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     4
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Modular programming in an object-oriented programming language, including string and vector manipulation, file I/O, bit operators, Boolean algebra, pointers, simple sorting and binary search, plus introductions to recursion and templates.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Contact Hour Distribution:
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     3 hours lecture and 1 lab.
                    </em>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Grading Restriction:
                    </em>
                    Letter grade only.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Credit Restriction:
                    </em>
                    Students who have received credit for
                    <a aria-label="COSC 202 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184326" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184326'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 202
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 230 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184327" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184327'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 230
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    may not receive subsequent credit for COSC 102.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 101 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184123" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184123'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ?                      COSC 101
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                    <em>

                    <h3>
                     COSC 312 - Algorithm Analysis and Automata
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Counting and combinatorics, with applications to the analysis of algorithms. Introduction to finite automata and regular languages, and to pushdown automata and context free grammars.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 311 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180790" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180790'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ?                      COSC 311
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 317 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182986" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182986'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 317
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 366 - Introduction to Cybersecurity
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    A broad introduction to cybersecurity concepts. The class will introduce basic topics core to understanding computer security including security goals, threat modeling, software security, operating system security, cryptography, network security, and human factors. Coursework focuses on helping students adapt a security aware mindset when designing, developing, and testing systems.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     Credit Restriction:
                    </em>
                    Cannot receive credit for both ECE 461 and COSC 366.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 302 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180789" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180789'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 302
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 307 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182985" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182985'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 307
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better, and either
                    <a aria-label="ECE 256 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183938" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183938'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ECE 256
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 230 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184327" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184327'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 230
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.

                    <h3>
                     COSC 361 - Operating Systems
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Threads, operating system structure, process management, scheduling, synchronization, deadlock, memory management, virtual memory and demand paging, file system management and implementation, mass storage structure, protection, security, and distributed systems.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 360 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180792" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180792'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 360
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 367 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182987" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182987'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 367
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 365 - Programming Languages and Systems
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Language paradigms (procedural, functional, object-oriented, logic), language design and implementation issues, and language issues related to parallelism.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 302 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180789" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180789'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 302
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">

                    <h3>
                     COSC 395 - Junior Seminar
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     1
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Presentations and discussions related to professional development, including registration, ethics, and current topics in computer science. Students will analyze aspects of scientific and technical writing and write a series of articles suitable for the general public.

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 401 - Senior Design Theory
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     2
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    A design course that focuses the student’s attention on professional practice, ethics, accumulated background of curricular components, and recent developments in the field. The focus is on teaching both the design process and design principles that allow students to utilize all of the above elements to effectively create designs for major design projects.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies Volunteer Core Requirement:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (OC)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 360 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180792" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180792'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 360
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 367 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182987" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182987'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 367
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>

                    <h3>
                     COSC 402 - Senior Design Practicum
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    A project-oriented course that requires teams of students to design a major project that incorporates the principles taught in
                    <a aria-label="COSC 401 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182990" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182990'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 401
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *. The design emphasis is directed to topics within the field of computer science.

                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies Volunteer Core Requirement:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (AOC)

                     </strong>
                    </em>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 101 - Introduction to Programming
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    An introduction to computational thinking and structured programming. Topics include problem solving and algorithm development with emphasis on conditional if/else statements, loop based iteration, and function calls. Students will also be given an overview of commonly used data structures such as arrays. Skills learned include designing a program to solving a problem, developing the algorithms needed, writing code to implement them, testing the code and correcting errors, as well as documenting how the code works.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     ENGL 118 - Honors: English Composition
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Grading scale and workload are same as in regular sequence though course proceeds at an accelerated pace. Emphasis on argumentation, critical inquiry, rhetorical analysis, and research methods. May include the study of a long work of literature or nonfiction in addition to a selection of interdisciplinary readings.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies Volunteer Core Requirement:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (WC)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies General Education Requirement through the 2021-2022 academic catalog:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (WC)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     Grading Restriction:
                    </em>
                    ABC/N grading only.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Credit Restriction:
                    </em>
                    Students with credit for
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 101 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180921" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180921'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 101
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *,
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 131 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180927" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180927'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 131
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *, or
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 198 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183351" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183351'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 198
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    * may not receive credit for ENGL 118*.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Comment(s):
                    </em>
                    ACT English and composite scores at or above 29 or SAT critical reading and composite scores of 680 and 1280 required. Students receiving a passing grade below B in ENGL 118* will complete the English Composition requirement by taking
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 102 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180922" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180922'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 102
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *. Students receiving a grade of B or better will complete their freshman English requirements by choosing
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 102 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180922" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180922'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 102
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *, a sophomore-level course in the English Department, or
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 355 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180964" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180964'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 355
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>

                    <h3>
                     ENGL 118 - Honors: English Composition
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Grading scale and workload are same as in regular sequence though course proceeds at an accelerated pace. Emphasis on argumentation, critical inquiry, rhetorical analysis, and research methods. May include the study of a long work of literature or nonfiction in addition to a selection of interdisciplinary readings.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies Volunteer Core Requirement:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (WC)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies General Education Requirement through the 2021-2022 academic catalog:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (WC)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     Grading Restriction:
                    </em>
                    ABC/N grading only.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Credit Restriction:
                    </em>
                    Students with credit for
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 101 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180921" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180921'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 101
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *,
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 131 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180927" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180927'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 131
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *, or
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 198 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183351" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183351'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 198
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    * may not receive credit for ENGL 118*.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Comment(s):
                    </em>
                    ACT English and composite scores at or above 29 or SAT critical reading and composite scores of 680 and 1280 required. Students receiving a passing grade below B in ENGL 118* will complete the English Composition requirement by taking
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 102 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180922" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180922'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 102
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *. Students receiving a grade of B or better will complete their freshman English requirements by choosing
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 102 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180922" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180922'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 102
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *, a sophomore-level course in the English Department, or
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 355 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180964" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180964'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 355
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *.

                    <h3>
                     ENGL 102 - English Composition II
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Advancing concepts introduced in
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 101 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180921" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180921'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 101
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *. Intensive writing instruction focused on inquiry and research. Strategies for formulating and investigating questions, locating and evaluating information, using varied sources and research methods, developing positions on intercultural and interdisciplinary issues from diverse texts (print, digital, and multimedia), and presenting research using appropriate rhetorical conventions.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies Volunteer Core Requirement:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (WC)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     <strong>
                      Satisfies General Education Requirement through the 2021-2022 academic catalog:
                     </strong>
                    </em>
                    (WC)
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     Grading Restriction:
                    </em>
                    ABC/N grading only.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Credit Restriction:
                    </em>
                    Students with credit for
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 132 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180928" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180928'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 132
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *,
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 298 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183398" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183398'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 298
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *, or
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 290 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183354" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183354'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 290
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    * may not receive credit for ENGL 102*.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 101 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180921" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180921'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 101
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Comment(s):
                    </em>
                    Students wishing additional help with writing should also register for
                    <a aria-label="ENGL 104 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180924" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180924'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ENGL 104
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 493 - Independent Study
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     1-3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Special project in area of student’s primary interest. Directed by computer science faculty, perhaps jointly with student’s faculty advisor. Intended for students with a specific project to pursue in conjunction with a faculty member. Project may be from a department other than computer science, in which case a faculty member from the appropriate department will help oversee the project.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     Repeatability:
                    </em>
                    May be repeated. Maximum 45 hours.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Credit Restriction:
                    </em>
                    Maximum of 6 hours may be applied toward the major.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Registration Permission:
                    </em>
                    Consent of instructor.
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>
              </div>

                    <h3>
                     COSC 422 - Applied Machine Learning
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Machine learning (ML) concepts; ML techniques for practical applications. ML approaches and learning methods in modeling and prediction of complex systems. Data acquisition and preprocessing, training, classification and prediction, modeling tools, and postprocessing and evaluation.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     Credit Restriction:
                    </em>
                    May not be applied toward the computer science or computer engineering majors.

                    <h3>
                     COSC 440 - Formal Foundations of Software Engineering
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     4
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Principles of analysis and design of information systems. Principles of program design and verification, formal objects, formal specifications.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 311 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180790" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180790'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 311
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 317 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182986" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182986'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ?                      COSC 317
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 482 - Theory of Computation
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Properties of finite automata/regular sets and push-down automata/context-free languages. Countability, diagonalization, and undecidability. Complexity, including the classes P and NP, NP-completeness, and reduction techniques.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 312 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182784" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182784'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 312
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>
              </div>

                     <a alt="Text Version" class="acalog-highlight-ignore acalog-icon" href="javascript:acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183936&amp;print', 'preview_course', 770, 530, 'yes')" title="Print Course (opens a new window)">
                      <span class="sr-only">
                       Print (opens a new window)
                      </span>
                     </a>
                    </div>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 452 - Computer Graphics
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Digital image synthesis, geometric modeling, and animation. Topics may include visual perception, displays and color spaces, frame buffers, affine transformations, data structures for geometric primitives, visible surface determination, shading and texturing, anti-aliasing computing light transport, rendering equation, shader programming, general purpose GPU programming, level of detail, curves and surfaces, and graphics hardware.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 462 - Parallel Programming
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Principles and practice of parallel computing; design, implementation, and evaluation of parallel programs for shared and distributed memory architectures, and vector processors. Sample topics include models of parallel computers, basic communication operations, performance and scalability of parallel systems, and programming techniques including multi-threading and message passing.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 360 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180792" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180792'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 360
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 367 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182987" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182987'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 367
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     ECE 453 - Introduction to Computer Networks
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Introduction to the design and implementation of computer networks. Topics to be covered include layered network architecture, physical media, data link protocols, network routing, transport layer, network programming interfaces such as sockets, and applications. Examples will be primarily based on protocols in the Internet.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 360 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180792" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180792'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ?                      COSC 360
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 367 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182987" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182987'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 367
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                    <em>

                    </em>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     ECE 462 - Cyber-Physical Systems Security
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Introduction to security challenges and techniques at both the physical layer and the cyber layer of important cyber-physical systems, including transportation systems, avionics, industrial automation systems, vehicular systems, medical systems, power systems, SCADA, nuclear plants, etc.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 102 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180785" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180785'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 102
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or equivalent with a grade of C or better, and
                    <a aria-label="ECE 313 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180811" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180811'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ECE 313
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="ECE 317 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182992" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182992'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ECE 317
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or equivalent with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Registration Restriction(s):
                    </em>
                    Junior standing or consent of the instructor.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     ECE 463 - Introduction to Datacenters
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Technologies and best practices in data center structure, management, and maintenance. Topics include datacenter structure and design, requirements, performance, security, power &amp; cooling, storage systems, networking, capacity/workload management, testing, and analysis. Students from engineering disciplines that can take this course include electrical, computer, industrial, mechanical, and nuclear engineering, and computer science.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <span class="acalog-permalink-inactive">
                     COSC 130
                    </span>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>

                   </div>
                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 453 - Data Visualization
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    The goal of this course is to develop a broad understanding of the principles, methods, and techniques for designing effective data visualizations. The course will span a wide range of topics related to interactive data visualization. The course will teach key elements of scientific visualization techniques, which graphically encode data with some physical or geometric correspondence, and information visualization techniques, which focus on abstract data without such correspondences such as symbolic, tabular, networked, hierarchical, or textual information sources. The course will follow a lecture/seminar style with discussion of assigned readings, as well as viewing of videos and hands-on experience with creating visualization tools.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <span class="acalog-permalink-inactive">
                     COSC 140
                    </span>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Recommended Background:
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 340 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180791" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180791'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 340
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    and
                    <a aria-label="COSC 452 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183936" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183936'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 452
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    .
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>
              </div>

                     COSC 461 - Introduction to Compilers
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     ECE 256 - Computer System Interfaces
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Introduction to design, implementation, and test of interfaces used in the construction of modern computing systems. Topics covered include memory and I/O devices, component interfaces, real-time operating system concepts, performance analysis, and optimizations. The lectures and lab assignments will cover both hardware and software elements needed to support target applications and interfaces. This includes physical layer and low-level protocol/information-format design and analysis. Other key elements covered in the class include direct memory access, timers, input/output synchronization, and interrupts. Emphasis is placed on hands-on and lab based exercises using an appropriate development system.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="ECE 255 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180809" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180809'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ECE 255
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>
              </div>
