                    <h3>
                     ECE 356 - Computer Systems Architecture
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Architecture and design of microcomputer systems with microprocessors or microcontrollers. Instruction set architectures, software interfaces, processor structures, memory hierarchy, and interfacing.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     ECE 455 - Embedded Systems Design
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Design and development of embedded systems for data acquisition and special-purpose computing systems. Topics covered include direct memory access, real-time software development, use of real-time operating systems, embedded system analysis, and embedded system networking. Students will learn approaches for improving embedded system performance in terms of power, speed and resource utilization.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="ECE 256 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183938" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183938'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ECE 256
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 370 - Introduction to Scientific Computing
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    The design, analysis, and implementation of numerical algorithms for solving problems in science and engineering. Emphasis on program design, including data structures, computational complexity, scientific computing environments, and high-performance software packages.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     Credit Restriction:
                    </em>
                    Students may not receive credit for both COSC 370 and
                    <a aria-label="MATH 371 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181646" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181646'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 371
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    .
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 202 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184326" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=184326'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 202
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better, and
                    <a aria-label="MATH 251 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181637" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181637'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 251
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="MATH 257 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181638" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181638'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 257
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.

                    <h3>
                     COSC 377 - Honors: Introduction to Scientific Computing
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>

                    Same as
                    <a aria-label="COSC 370 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180794" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180794'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ?                      COSC 370

                    with additional honors project.

                    </em>

                     Credit Restriction:
                    </em>
                    Students may not receive credit for both COSC 377 and
                    <a aria-label="MATH 371 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181646" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181646'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ?                      MATH 371

                    </span>

'&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 202
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better, and
                    <a aria-label="MATH 251 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181637" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181637'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ?                      MATH 251
                    </a>

                    <a aria-label="MATH 257 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181638" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181638'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ?                     <h3>
                     MATH 231 - Differential Equations I
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    First course emphasizing solution techniques. Includes first-order equations and applications, theory of linear equations, equations with constant coefficients, Laplace transforms, and series solutions.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="MATH 142 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181626" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181626'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ?                      MATH 142
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    * or
                    <a aria-label="MATH 148 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181628" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181628'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ?                      MATH 148
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    *.

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     MATH 241 - Calculus III
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     4
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Calculus of functions in two or more dimensions. Includes solid analytic geometry, partial differentiation, multiple integration, and selected topics in vector calculus.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="MATH 142 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181626" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181626'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 142
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    * or
                    <a aria-label="MATH 148 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181628" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181628'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 148
                    </a>

                    <h3>
                     COSC 420 - Biologically-Inspired Computation
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Recent developments in computational methods inspired by nature, such as neural networks, genetic algorithms, evolutionary programming, ant-swarm optimization, artificial immune systems, swarm intelligence, cellular automata, multi-agent systems, cooperation, and competition.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>

                    </em>
                    Completion of core courses.

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 421 - Computational Cognitive Neuroscience
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Survey of computational cognitive neuroscience. The focus is on the neuroscience of cognitive processes, including perception, categorization, memory, language, action, and executive control. Course work makes use of computer simulations of neural networks to model cognitive processes and to test hypotheses about their neural implementations.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     Credit Restriction:
                    </em>
                    Students cannot receive credit for both COSC 421 and COSC 521.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Recommended Background:
                    </em>
                    Senior standing.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 425 - Introduction to Machine Learning
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Machine learning is concerned with computer programs that automatically improve their performance through experience. This course covers the theory and practice of machine learning from a variety of perspectives. We cover topics such as clustering, decision trees, neural network learning, statistical learning methods, Bayesian learning methods, dimension reduction, kernel methods, and reinforcement learning. Programming assignments include implementation and hands-on experiments with various learning algorithms.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>

                    <h3>
                     ECE 471 - Introduction to Pattern Recognition
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Introduction to statistical decision theory, adaptive classifiers, and supervised and unsupervised learning. Students will explore the application of these techniques in areas of current interest, such as face recognition, speech processing, remote sensing, data mining, and bioinformatics.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>

                    <h3>
                     COSC 434 - Network Security
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    In-depth introduction to core Internet and wireless technologies, related security concerns, common security vulnerabilities, and good security practices. Hands-on experience exploiting network protocols and communications, and setting up secure network connections.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 445 - Fundamentals of Digital Archeology
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    This is an advanced topic course focused on developing multi-disciplinary skills of discovering, retrieving, analyzing, and presenting operational data. Students will use critical thinking and intense practice solving real-world problems to recognize and address key operational issues: the lack of context, missing observations, and incorrect values. At the end of the course students will be able to discover operational data, to retrieve and store it, to recover context, to estimate the impact of missing events, to identify unreliable or incorrect values, and to present the results.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     Recommended Background:
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 340 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180791" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180791'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 340
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    ,
                    <a aria-label="COSC 370 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180794" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180794'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 370
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    ,
                    <a aria-label="ECE 313 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180811" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180811'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ECE 313
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    .
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 466 - Software Security
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    An in-depth introduction to software security. The focus is on identifying vulnerabilities in software, exploiting vulnerabilities in software, and software development best practices for avoiding vulnerabilities during the design, implementation, testing, and deployment of software. Coursework involves hands on experience exploiting software vulnerabilities to increase understanding, awareness, and appreciation of software vulnerabilities.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     Credit Restriction:
                    </em>
                    Students cannot receive credit for both COSC 466 and COSC 566 (see graduate catalog for course description).
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 366 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183934" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183934'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 366
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>

                    <h3>
                     COSC 469 - Human Factors in Cybersecurity
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    A broad introduction to human-computer interaction (HCI) and its impact on the theory and practice of cybersecurity. Topics include the research methods in HCI, ethics, authentication, usable secure communication, phishing, usable cryptographic libraries, inclusivity/diversity in system design, and human-aware policy creation. Coursework focuses on helping students adapt a human-aware mindset regarding the design, implementation, and use of cybersecurity tools and principles.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     Credit Restriction:
                    </em>
                    Students cannot receive credit for both COSC 469 and COSC 569 (see graduate catalog for course description).
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 366 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183934" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=183934'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 366
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>
              </div>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     ECE 459 - Secure and Trustworthy Computer Hardware Design
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    In-depth introduction to a range of new developments for the design of secure and trustworthy computer hardware. Topics covered include physical and invasive attack models, side-channel analysis (SCA) attacks, physical unclonable functions, hardware-based random number generators, watermarking of intellectual property (IP) blocks, FPGA security, passive and active metering for piracy prevention, and hardware Trojan detection and isolation.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="ECE 255 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180809" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180809'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ECE 255
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 360 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180792" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180792'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 360
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 367 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182987" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182987'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 367
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>

                    <h3>
                     ECE 462 - Cyber-Physical Systems Security
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Introduction to security challenges and techniques at both the physical layer and the cyber layer of important cyber-physical systems, including transportation systems, avionics, industrial automation systems, vehicular systems, medical systems, power systems, SCADA, nuclear plants, etc.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 102 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180785" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180785'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 102
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or equivalent with a grade of C or better, and
                    <a aria-label="ECE 313 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180811" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180811'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ECE 313
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="ECE 317 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182992" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182992'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ECE 317
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or equivalent with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Registration Restriction(s):
                    </em>
                    Junior standing or consent of the instructor.
                    <br/>
                   </div>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     ECE 469 - Mobile and Embedded Systems Security
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Introduction to vulnerabilities and threat vectors associated with mobile and embedded devices, such as smartphones, wearable devices, and IoT devices. Topics include security features and limitations of mobile operating systems, secure programming, mobile location and activity privacy, user/device authentication, IoT wireless security, side-channel attacks on mobile/wearable devices, and security and privacy breaches on smart home devices. Coursework focuses on improving knowledge and awareness of mobile and embedded systems’ security issues, through individual homework assignments and an intensive group project involving hands-on research.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="COSC 360 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180792" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180792'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 360
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="COSC 367 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182987" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182987'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     COSC 367
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                  </td>
                 </tr>
                </tbody>
               </table>

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     ECE 471 - Introduction to Pattern Recognition
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Introduction to statistical decision theory, adaptive classifiers, and supervised and unsupervised learning. Students will explore the application of these techniques in areas of current interest, such as face recognition, speech processing, remote sensing, data mining, and bioinformatics.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="ECE 313 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180811" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180811'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ECE 313
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="ECE 317 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182992" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182992'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ECE 317
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="MATH 323 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181643" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181643'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 323

                   <div>
                    <h3>
                     COSC 425 - Introduction to Machine Learning
                    </h3>
                    <strong>
                     3
                    </strong>
                    <strong>
                     Credit Hours
                    </strong>
                    <hr/>
                    Machine learning is concerned with computer programs that automatically improve their performance through experience. This course covers the theory and practice of machine learning from a variety of perspectives. We cover topics such as clustering, decision trees, neural network learning, statistical learning methods, Bayesian learning methods, dimension reduction, kernel methods, and reinforcement learning. Programming assignments include implementation and hands-on experiments with various learning algorithms.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                    <em>
                     (RE) Prerequisite(s):
                    </em>
                    <a aria-label="ECE 313 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180811" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=180811'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ECE 313
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="ECE 317 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182992" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=182992'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     ECE 317
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="MATH 323 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181643" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181643'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 323
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better; and
                    <a aria-label="MATH 251 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181637" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181637'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 251
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    or
                    <a aria-label="MATH 257 opens a new window" href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181638" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=34&amp;coid=181638'+((location.search.match(/&amp;print/i)) ? '&amp;print' : '')+'', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" target="_blank">
                     MATH 257
                    </a>
                    <span style="display: none !important">
                    </span>
                    with a grade of C or better.
                    <br/>
                    <em>
                     Comment(s):
                    </em>
                    Prior knowledge may satisfy prerequisite with consent of instructor.
                    <br/>
                   </div>
